body:
@ijuma Thoughts on protecting against this? Doesn't seem like there's much to be done that is automated since running against 0.10.2 doesn't make sense for a lot of patches. I can think of 2 options:

1. Add CI for it, but have it conditional based on some flag in the PR that indicates what branches we want to test against.
2. Just require committers to run the full tests on each branch they merged. (I used to do this until the test time got so high it became kind of impractical.)
